Bertrand, better known as "Krimer", started with producing in August 2012. Early in 2013 one of his first tracks has caught the eye of promoter DUPLOC. Throughout that year a few of his tracks have been uploaded on DUPLOCpromotions and the quality of his productions were remarkably expanding.

By delivering quality on a regular base he gained some respect within the scene. His tracks are being played out by established names in the scene such as, ENiGMA Dubz, Airvalue, BloodThinnerz, DJ SnipaZ, Benzmixer,..

At the end of 2013, he had his first official release on the "Recommended by DUPLOC EP" in co-operation with Dubstar Records. Only 2 weeks after his first album "Who's The Hardest EP" dropped on Southside Dubstars UK. His next album "Krimer - Impact EP" is forthcoming on DPLC Recordings, a dubstep label, strictly releasing exclusive content, established by DUPLOC. Some other acknowledged labels, such as BassClash, Styx,.. are also keeping an eye out for this upcoming producer.

While the originality of his productions are still expanding, he's also receiving several bookings. In march 2014, Krimer played in Belgium at the 'Quake invites Monsters' opening for Shiverz, Bukez Finezt, SubFiltronik...

A fast upcoming newcomer in the scene which definitely will be making some more impact in the scene in
